               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380820-name-1316" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1316" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1316" type="surname" value="MILLS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1316" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY MILLS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live with Mr. Thomas Smith, at the Coach and Horses, in High-street, Shadwell. About six o'clock, on the 17th of August, the prisoner came and called for half a pint of beer—I served her with it in a pint pot—she sat by the side of the bar, and there was a quart pot that some one had left-when I turned she and the pot were gone—I went and found her with the quart pot, and took her back—this is my master's pot.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380820-name-1317" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1317" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1317" type="surname" value="MARTIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1317" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES MARTIN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I took the prisoner, and found the quart pot under her shawl, under her arm.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183808200199"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. I had no shawl on—there was full half a pint of beer in the pot—I just took it outside the door to give to my daughter. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. there was a little beer in the bottom of the pot—she was one hundred and fifty yards from the house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. Some persons were drinking out of a quart pot—they went away and said, "Old lady, there is a little beer for you"—I emptied the half pint into the quart pot, and went to look for. my daughter outside—I was not two doors from the house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">JURY</hi>. to <hi rend="smallCaps">JAMES MARTIN</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was the pot entirely covered with the Shawl? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes.</p>
